WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:10.400
(Support Admin Watch on kisskh.one)

00:00:11.512 --> 00:00:14.181
This is the biggest event
of the century!

00:00:14.281 --> 00:00:17.518
I can't believe they are

00:00:18.018 --> 00:00:20.821
going to make their debut
in Japan so soon!

00:00:33.467 --> 00:00:36.003
- Here...
- It's coming...

00:00:47.381 --> 00:00:48.515
Ryo's expression is perfect!

00:00:56.823 --> 00:01:00.460
That was TORINNER, making their
first appearance on Japanese TV.

00:01:00.527 --> 00:01:03.230
Please say a few words
to the Japanese audience.

00:01:03.297 --> 00:01:05.198
- Okay.
- Hi, everyone.

00:01:05.265 --> 00:01:06.400
- We're TORINNER.
- We're TORINNER.

00:01:06.466 --> 00:01:08.035
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

00:01:08.368 --> 00:01:09.937
They're so handsome!

00:01:10.404 --> 00:01:12.773
You just debuted in Korea last month

00:01:12.839 --> 00:01:14.675
and your Asia tour
was a huge success.

00:01:14.741 --> 00:01:16.143
You're very popular!

00:01:16.209 --> 00:01:17.210
Thank you.

00:01:17.277 --> 00:01:19.346
- It's all thanks to our fans.
- Oh, my gosh!

00:01:19.413 --> 00:01:20.480
Ryo is so handsome today, too!

00:01:20.547 --> 00:01:21.882
- Oh, my gosh!
- We'll do our best

00:01:21.949 --> 00:01:24.184
to deliver a bouquet
of music to our fans.

00:01:24.251 --> 00:01:25.752
Please root for us.

00:01:26.353 --> 00:01:27.688
- Please root for us.
- Please root for us.

00:01:29.957 --> 00:01:32.426
- Do your best!
- Do your best! You're so hot!

00:01:35.729 --> 00:01:37.130
Attention seeker.

00:01:37.230 --> 00:01:38.832
POPULAR K-POP GROUP'S
FIRST APPEARANCE ON JAPANESE TV

00:01:40.601 --> 00:01:42.202
They've gotten so good.

00:01:42.302 --> 00:01:43.470
Their skills are insane.

00:01:45.372 --> 00:01:48.642
Yes, you might not stand a chance.

00:01:48.709 --> 00:01:50.811
They are much better than you
in terms of

00:01:50.877 --> 00:01:52.713
performance, looks,
and above all, charisma.

00:01:52.779 --> 00:01:55.782
Hey, Mr. Azuma! How can you say that?

00:01:57.718 --> 00:02:00.787
We've come all this way to Japan,
but TORINNER...

00:02:00.854 --> 00:02:04.524
After all, we're the leftovers
that weren't chosen there.

00:02:07.427 --> 00:02:10.330
Guys, you shouldn't give up.

00:02:10.397 --> 00:02:12.866
Well, some things just can't
be overcome with effort alone.

00:02:12.933 --> 00:02:16.436
You're lucky to learn this truth
about life at such a young age.

00:02:17.104 --> 00:02:18.672
Mr. Azuma!

00:02:19.740 --> 00:02:22.542
Ryo is as cool as ever, though.

00:02:22.609 --> 00:02:23.844
At the start of your day

00:02:24.077 --> 00:02:27.314
to cheer you up while traveling.

00:02:27.381 --> 00:02:30.017
Listen to it to motivate yourself
before studying...

00:02:30.083 --> 00:02:31.718
Don't worry about it.

00:02:31.785 --> 00:02:35.789
We performed at TGC,
and we got a lot of media attention.

00:02:36.456 --> 00:02:39.693
Also, you'll be interviewed
tomorrow morning

00:02:39.760 --> 00:02:42.496
and you'll record a music show
next week.

00:02:42.562 --> 00:02:44.231
Yes, that's right.

00:02:44.297 --> 00:02:48.568
Right? So sleep well tonight,
and do your best tomorrow.

00:02:49.403 --> 00:02:51.405
- Yes, ma'am!
- Yes, ma'am!

00:02:52.706 --> 00:02:53.740
Well done.

00:02:55.409 --> 00:02:56.410
She made them perform

00:02:56.510 --> 00:02:58.378
on a TV show
as soon as they arrived in Japan

00:02:58.612 --> 00:03:00.480
to show people how busy they are.

00:03:00.547 --> 00:03:02.182
That's our Ms. Park!

00:03:02.282 --> 00:03:03.583
You flatter me.

00:03:03.684 --> 00:03:05.652
It's all thanks
to your influence, Mr. Choi.

00:03:08.989 --> 00:03:11.958
Talents gather where the money is,
and money gathers talents.

00:03:12.793 --> 00:03:17.097
The one who has these two
has all the power.

00:03:18.065 --> 00:03:19.666
It's cruel, but this is the reality.

00:03:20.200 --> 00:03:21.535
You're right.

00:03:21.601 --> 00:03:22.602
However

00:03:23.704 --> 00:03:27.974
the person who holds the power
is responsible for shaping the era.

00:03:29.209 --> 00:03:33.280
Deliver hope
and excitement to the world.

00:03:34.514 --> 00:03:38.552
This is what you and TORINNER
should do in the future.

00:03:39.152 --> 00:03:40.153
Understand?

00:03:40.454 --> 00:03:41.555
It's your life's purpose.

00:03:42.155 --> 00:03:44.124
Certainly, sir.

00:03:48.428 --> 00:03:50.097
Guys, let's give it our all!

00:03:50.197 --> 00:03:51.732
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:03:55.802 --> 00:03:58.839
You'll be interviewed
as a promising new group

00:03:59.439 --> 00:04:00.774
so be as charming as possible.

00:04:01.408 --> 00:04:02.442
- Okay!
- Okay!

00:04:02.943 --> 00:04:04.644
I'll go check us in.

00:04:05.112 --> 00:04:07.781
Isn't this our first interview?

00:04:08.381 --> 00:04:10.317
- Yes!
- That's right!

00:04:10.383 --> 00:04:11.952
Guys, don't be nervous.

00:04:12.119 --> 00:04:13.186
- Stay calm.
- What?

00:04:14.054 --> 00:04:15.055
Hey!

00:04:15.122 --> 00:04:17.524
You're the one walking so stiffly.

00:04:17.624 --> 00:04:19.893
What? The interview is canceled?

00:04:22.095 --> 00:04:24.531
I'm sorry, but why so suddenly?

00:04:24.631 --> 00:04:27.434
Sorry, our plan changed suddenly.

00:04:27.501 --> 00:04:29.436
But you asked to interview us--

00:04:29.536 --> 00:04:31.371
That's true, but...

00:04:31.972 --> 00:04:33.306
We'll interview them next time.

00:04:33.373 --> 00:04:34.441
What? Wait.

00:04:36.610 --> 00:04:37.778
I'm sorry!

00:04:37.844 --> 00:04:40.614
No, this isn't your fault, Minase.

00:04:42.382 --> 00:04:44.618
Still, why was it suddenly canceled?

00:04:44.718 --> 00:04:46.586
Here we go again.

00:04:48.155 --> 00:04:50.056
Do you mean Park is behind it?

00:04:50.123 --> 00:04:52.092
Weren't all your interviews
in Korea canceled, too?

00:04:52.159 --> 00:04:54.795
They've decided to break into Japan

00:04:54.861 --> 00:04:56.763
so they're probably
targeting you again.

00:04:57.030 --> 00:04:58.565
How can they do that?

00:05:00.734 --> 00:05:01.735
Dear Miss Minase

00:05:01.835 --> 00:05:02.903
The group's performance
next week is canceled.

00:05:02.969 --> 00:05:04.704
- No way!
- What's wrong?

00:05:06.106 --> 00:05:08.341
The recording of the music show
next week...

00:05:09.743 --> 00:05:11.545
They want to cancel it.

00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:15.615
- No way.
- Seriously?

00:05:15.682 --> 00:05:16.850
The music show, too?

00:05:16.917 --> 00:05:20.554
Well, there's no point staying here.
Let's go back and have a meeting.

00:05:25.559 --> 00:05:28.061
Hey, fancy seeing you guys here.

00:05:29.095 --> 00:05:32.165
I remember your group has
a weird name. What was it again?

00:05:32.499 --> 00:05:33.900
Let me think...

00:05:35.235 --> 00:05:36.236
"NAME"?

00:05:37.737 --> 00:05:38.939
"NENDO"?

00:05:42.542 --> 00:05:43.710
Yuya.

00:05:45.312 --> 00:05:46.413
You seem to be doing well.

00:05:51.384 --> 00:05:54.054
Are you Mr. Azuma, NAZE's producer?

00:05:55.755 --> 00:05:57.557
It's an honor to meet you.

00:05:59.359 --> 00:06:00.360
Hello.

00:06:01.828 --> 00:06:04.464
Did you watch
our performance last night?

00:06:05.065 --> 00:06:08.568
They asked us to perform live
on our first day in Japan

00:06:08.635 --> 00:06:11.905
so it was tough to arrange it.
What about you?

00:06:13.707 --> 00:06:15.008
Are you here for an interview?

00:06:15.609 --> 00:06:19.112
Yes. Strangely enough,
it was canceled at the last minute.

00:06:21.882 --> 00:06:26.620
Isn't it an adult's responsibility
to show the reality

00:06:27.654 --> 00:06:29.289
to kids who aren't qualified
to dream?

00:06:31.057 --> 00:06:32.259
Isn't that rude...

00:06:33.193 --> 00:06:34.594
I agree with you.

00:06:39.966 --> 00:06:41.968
How admirable.

00:06:42.035 --> 00:06:44.471
I can't believe
you still aim to be idols.

00:06:45.338 --> 00:06:48.842
But be honest with me.
Isn't it getting tough?

00:06:52.045 --> 00:06:54.581
I'll put you out of your misery soon.

00:06:59.519 --> 00:07:02.622
Big companies have big expectations.
It must be tough.

00:07:03.189 --> 00:07:05.592
For both you and your boys.

00:07:06.559 --> 00:07:08.561
Be careful not to be crushed.

00:07:17.737 --> 00:07:21.374
I'm sorry this had to happen
when we've finally met after so long.

00:07:28.448 --> 00:07:29.482
Yuya.

00:07:34.621 --> 00:07:36.656
All our interviews
have been canceled!

00:07:37.190 --> 00:07:39.592
What should we do?
They won't gain traction!

00:07:40.193 --> 00:07:42.262
That means I won't be able
to pay off my debt!

00:07:42.329 --> 00:07:44.597
Oh, stop panicking.

00:07:44.664 --> 00:07:46.466
That darn woman...

00:07:47.500 --> 00:07:50.870
She got in my way in Korea,
and now in Japan as well?

00:07:53.139 --> 00:07:56.977
Darn it! There's nowhere to run.

00:07:57.077 --> 00:07:59.946
Excuse me!
Please have a look at this!

00:08:01.581 --> 00:08:03.183
"A 10-Round Battle

00:08:03.249 --> 00:08:04.551
Between TORINNER and NAZE"?

00:08:05.485 --> 00:08:07.354
We lost all the visual battles.

00:08:07.754 --> 00:08:10.090
We also lost all the fashion battles.

00:08:10.156 --> 00:08:12.258
Height, vocal skills

00:08:12.325 --> 00:08:14.527
dancing skills, physical abilities

00:08:14.594 --> 00:08:16.663
intellect, masculinity

00:08:16.963 --> 00:08:18.398
potential...

00:08:18.465 --> 00:08:19.699
We lost in all categories.

00:08:19.866 --> 00:08:21.234
They even have over ten times

00:08:21.334 --> 00:08:22.402
more followers than NAZE.

00:08:22.469 --> 00:08:23.470
It almost feels refreshing

00:08:23.570 --> 00:08:25.005
to be defeated so badly.

00:08:26.006 --> 00:08:27.107
That woman...

00:08:27.340 --> 00:08:29.275
Park Ji-soo used
her money and influence

00:08:29.342 --> 00:08:31.244
and had someone publish
this fake article!

00:08:32.312 --> 00:08:33.680
I won't forgive her!

00:08:33.747 --> 00:08:35.382
That's definitely it!

00:08:35.448 --> 00:08:37.851
It's so unfair
for a big agency to do this!

00:08:37.951 --> 00:08:38.952
Unfair!

00:08:39.019 --> 00:08:40.620
"CEO of NAZE's agency

00:08:40.687 --> 00:08:42.222
Causes a Scene at the Airport!"

00:08:42.288 --> 00:08:44.591
"Is This Her Way of Sabotaging
TORINNER, Their Rivals?"

00:08:44.657 --> 00:08:46.159
I'll punish the traitor!

00:08:47.127 --> 00:08:49.329
Sabotage? That's an exaggeration.

00:08:49.729 --> 00:08:52.265
"Rumor has it that TORINNER's Ryo,
the best-looking man

00:08:52.332 --> 00:08:55.301
of the century,
has a younger brother in NAZE."

00:08:55.368 --> 00:08:57.570
It's not a rumor. He actually exists.

00:08:57.670 --> 00:08:59.739
They don't look
very much alike, though.

00:08:59.839 --> 00:09:01.307
"However, our reporter couldn't find

00:09:01.408 --> 00:09:04.177
any member
who looked like Ryo," or so it says.

00:09:04.344 --> 00:09:05.345
What?

00:09:07.147 --> 00:09:10.984
Are your eyes just for show?

00:09:14.154 --> 00:09:15.622
Compare looks.

00:09:19.526 --> 00:09:22.896
Wait, so this old lady is the CEO
of another group?

00:09:22.962 --> 00:09:24.130
The one we saw back then?

00:09:24.197 --> 00:09:25.598
- Seriously?
- Hey, look at this.

00:09:25.698 --> 00:09:27.033
TRAITOR

00:09:27.100 --> 00:09:28.635
- What's that?
- Isn't it crazy?

00:09:28.701 --> 00:09:30.703
- That's horrible!
- It's insane!

00:09:31.704 --> 00:09:33.606
I've never even heard of NAZE.

00:09:33.673 --> 00:09:36.843
TORINNER's rival?
Who do they think they are?

00:09:37.210 --> 00:09:38.211
Right?

00:09:38.311 --> 00:09:41.581
I can't believe brothers with
the same parents can be so different.

00:09:42.182 --> 00:09:45.618
I guess you took
all the good qualities.

00:09:48.888 --> 00:09:50.390
Yuya has many good qualities.

00:09:50.657 --> 00:09:51.658
What?

00:09:51.724 --> 00:09:55.962
Besides, weren't you
his fellow trainee a while ago?

00:09:57.063 --> 00:09:59.165
Don't talk
about your friend like this.

00:09:59.232 --> 00:10:01.101
Come again? My friend?

00:10:02.068 --> 00:10:05.305
What a nice big brother you are!
Fellow trainees?

00:10:05.605 --> 00:10:07.740
Friends? Don't be ridiculous.

00:10:07.807 --> 00:10:10.276
Don't lump me in
with mediocre guys like them!

00:10:10.710 --> 00:10:14.547
And Ryo, maybe you think
you're TORINNER's center

00:10:14.614 --> 00:10:16.116
but I won't accept it!

00:10:16.182 --> 00:10:17.250
I refuse to!

00:10:17.317 --> 00:10:19.886
All you have are your looks.

00:10:19.953 --> 00:10:21.721
You just got lucky with your genes.

00:10:21.821 --> 00:10:23.656
Hey, Yeon-woo, stop it.

00:10:24.157 --> 00:10:25.758
Don't let it get to your head

00:10:26.659 --> 00:10:28.094
or I'll crush you.

00:10:33.299 --> 00:10:34.968
Just stop it.

00:10:37.971 --> 00:10:39.906
We've decided on
your debut song in Japan.

00:10:41.141 --> 00:10:43.042
So, it's Japan after Korea,
after all.

00:10:43.143 --> 00:10:44.844
What? Got a problem?

00:10:44.944 --> 00:10:48.181
No, it's just...
We were told it was the US at first.

00:10:48.281 --> 00:10:49.482
Why Japan?

00:10:51.851 --> 00:10:54.154
Loyalty is a national trait
of the Japanese people.

00:10:55.021 --> 00:10:57.524
You'll first build
a strong fandom in Japan

00:10:57.590 --> 00:10:59.792
and that will take you
to your worldwide debut later.

00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:01.161
- Yes.
- Yes.

00:11:02.028 --> 00:11:04.330
Of course, you must get first place
in the debut ranking.

00:11:05.665 --> 00:11:09.636
So from this moment onwards,
you must not

00:11:10.136 --> 00:11:11.938
make any mistake

00:11:13.106 --> 00:11:17.177
before your debut.

00:11:17.744 --> 00:11:19.679
Aside from your performance

00:11:19.746 --> 00:11:23.116
everything from your traveling attire
to the angle of your smile

00:11:23.183 --> 00:11:25.151
must be controlled perfectly.

00:11:25.518 --> 00:11:26.519
Do you hear me?

00:11:26.853 --> 00:11:28.321
- Yes.
- Yes.

00:11:28.988 --> 00:11:30.089
Come with me.

00:11:33.593 --> 00:11:35.028
Only Ryo again?

00:11:36.729 --> 00:11:39.632
Actually, I want you
to do something for me.

00:11:43.169 --> 00:11:46.472
It's making me more depressed
when they compare us like this.

00:11:50.443 --> 00:11:53.012
RUMOR HAS IT THAT TORINNER'S RYO
HAS A YOUNGER BROTHER IN NAZE

00:11:56.983 --> 00:11:58.284
- Ryo!
- What?

00:11:59.652 --> 00:12:01.087
- What's up?
- Why are you here?

00:12:01.554 --> 00:12:03.856
Ryo said he wanted to see you all.

00:12:07.160 --> 00:12:11.497
I'm sorry for the rude remarks
earlier today.

00:12:12.365 --> 00:12:15.668
No, it wasn't your fault, Ryo.
Right, guys?

00:12:15.735 --> 00:12:18.271
That's right! It was Yeon-woo
and Ms. Park.

00:12:18.338 --> 00:12:21.140
They've always been
nasty people. Right?

00:12:21.207 --> 00:12:22.675
- Exactly!
- It's okay.

00:12:22.742 --> 00:12:24.077
Thank you, guys.

00:12:24.143 --> 00:12:25.445
Leave.

00:12:27.880 --> 00:12:30.850
You're just apologizing
to make yourself feel better.

00:12:30.950 --> 00:12:32.885
We don't have time to entertain
your self-satisfaction.

00:12:32.952 --> 00:12:36.289
Yuya, don't talk
to your brother like that.

00:12:40.159 --> 00:12:41.728
I didn't just come to apologize.

00:12:42.895 --> 00:12:44.163
I came with a great offer.

00:12:44.764 --> 00:12:45.932
Great offer?

00:12:48.167 --> 00:12:51.271
Will you perform at our live
performance as our special guests?

00:12:51.904 --> 00:12:53.306
Live performance?

00:12:53.406 --> 00:12:54.607
- Really?
- Live performance?

00:12:54.674 --> 00:12:56.843
It'll be our first live performance
in Japan

00:12:56.909 --> 00:12:59.579
so we want to use this opportunity
to liven things up with NAZE.

00:13:00.213 --> 00:13:02.448
- Isn't this great?
- Really?

00:13:02.515 --> 00:13:06.152
There's no way
Ms. Park will allow that.

00:13:06.252 --> 00:13:07.253
Impossible.

00:13:08.087 --> 00:13:11.424
Ms. Park will be back in Korea
by then, so she won't be here.

00:13:11.758 --> 00:13:13.960
So we want to do it in secret.

00:13:14.027 --> 00:13:17.864
Really? What about money, then?
Who will pay the expenses?

00:13:17.930 --> 00:13:22.935
Our agency is hosting this event,
so you can just perform as guests.

00:13:23.002 --> 00:13:24.904
In other words, it's free?

00:13:25.505 --> 00:13:26.706
It's free.

00:13:27.240 --> 00:13:29.542
Ryo, dear!

00:13:29.642 --> 00:13:33.313
I knew you'd be the only one
I could count on! Thank you--

00:13:33.379 --> 00:13:34.847
There's no way we're doing that!

00:13:38.351 --> 00:13:39.619
I bet this time they'll write that

00:13:39.819 --> 00:13:43.189
TORINNER is also way better than us
in live performances, right?

00:13:45.124 --> 00:13:46.392
Yuya.

00:13:46.893 --> 00:13:50.596
Don't make fools
of my friends anymore.

00:13:53.499 --> 00:13:55.601
Isn't that great? Let's do it.

00:13:56.369 --> 00:13:57.370
Mr. Azuma.

00:13:57.470 --> 00:13:59.939
We can promote ourselves
to TORINNER's fans, and it's free.

00:14:00.039 --> 00:14:01.708
We have to do it. Right, CEO?

00:14:04.310 --> 00:14:05.878
Well, I suppose so, but...

00:14:07.347 --> 00:14:10.116
Thank you for the great offer,
Yuya's big brother.

00:14:12.719 --> 00:14:13.786
I'm Ryo.

00:14:16.189 --> 00:14:19.926
I'm very sorry
about upsetting you today.

00:14:20.626 --> 00:14:21.994
Don't worry about it.

00:14:25.565 --> 00:14:28.034
I talked to Mr. Azuma. They'll do it.

00:14:28.134 --> 00:14:29.369
Okay.

00:14:30.303 --> 00:14:33.005
Once I get them on the stage

00:14:33.072 --> 00:14:34.574
it'll practically be over for them.

00:14:35.708 --> 00:14:37.176
What do you mean?

00:14:40.313 --> 00:14:43.516
Our company has
many world-famous groups.

00:14:44.283 --> 00:14:46.252
As a junior to these groups

00:14:46.319 --> 00:14:48.421
their fans will automatically root
for TORINNER

00:14:49.088 --> 00:14:51.257
when you make your debut in Japan.

00:14:52.291 --> 00:14:53.993
Now, you only need to show them

00:14:54.060 --> 00:14:56.696
your performance
is in a totally different league.

00:14:58.197 --> 00:15:00.733
It should be easy enough
with your true abilities.

00:15:02.702 --> 00:15:05.138
NAZE is nothing more
but our group's leftovers.

00:15:06.005 --> 00:15:08.007
Even if they sing
and dance with all their might

00:15:08.641 --> 00:15:10.476
the audience will remain silent.

00:15:13.079 --> 00:15:16.215
They'll be torn to shreds
on social media.

00:15:17.450 --> 00:15:21.287
That will be the end for them.

00:15:27.126 --> 00:15:30.296
Once they shamelessly step on stage,
it's the end for them.

00:15:30.730 --> 00:15:33.399
What a nasty prank!

00:15:36.869 --> 00:15:39.005
You must be Ryo. Hello.

00:15:40.273 --> 00:15:44.444
I'm a reporter for this magazine.
My name is Kazamatsuri.

00:15:45.378 --> 00:15:47.713
A silent audience.

00:15:47.780 --> 00:15:50.483
My heart breaks
just from imagining that.

00:15:50.550 --> 00:15:54.153
Oh, poor NAZE!

00:15:56.355 --> 00:15:57.457
Ms. Park.

00:15:58.324 --> 00:16:01.060
Here is the invoice.

00:16:09.235 --> 00:16:12.672
Only a handful of people
can achieve their dreams.

00:16:13.105 --> 00:16:17.343
It's a kindness
to make them realize that early.

00:16:20.780 --> 00:16:22.882
10 DAYS TO NAZE'S
FIRST LIVE PERFORMANCE

00:16:22.949 --> 00:16:25.585
Let's do our best
for NAZE's first live performance.

00:16:26.118 --> 00:16:27.553
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:16:27.620 --> 00:16:30.089
I want to send a video of our
performance to my sister in Korea.

00:16:30.156 --> 00:16:31.891
- Sure!
- I'd like to show my family

00:16:31.958 --> 00:16:33.159
in Thailand, too.

00:16:33.226 --> 00:16:35.328
They sent me some messages yesterday.

00:16:35.394 --> 00:16:36.996
I believe you can make
your dreams come true!

00:16:37.063 --> 00:16:39.065
I'm sure they'll be delighted.

00:16:39.465 --> 00:16:42.134
- Gosh!
- Nice!

00:16:42.201 --> 00:16:44.103
- So cute!
- It really is in Thai!

00:16:44.537 --> 00:16:47.206
- Right!
- Yuya? Are you okay?

00:16:47.840 --> 00:16:48.941
Yes, I'm okay.

00:16:51.911 --> 00:16:56.782
Let's show Ryo
how much we've improved.

00:16:58.451 --> 00:17:00.086
Yes. Thank you, Turn.

00:17:01.921 --> 00:17:05.691
They'll use the power of their agency
to mobilize a large crowd.

00:17:05.958 --> 00:17:08.094
That means we'll be
in unfamiliar territory.

00:17:08.194 --> 00:17:10.830
You'll be surrounded by enemies
when you're on the stage.

00:17:10.930 --> 00:17:13.165
Really? That's rough.

00:17:14.033 --> 00:17:16.802
Those people know nothing about you.

00:17:16.869 --> 00:17:19.305
So, what should you do
to make them interested in you?

00:17:19.772 --> 00:17:21.607
To do so, the most important thing is

00:17:21.707 --> 00:17:24.010
to know yourselves.

00:17:24.076 --> 00:17:25.778
Know ourselves?

00:17:25.845 --> 00:17:28.247
How do others see you?

00:17:28.314 --> 00:17:30.716
What are your selling points?

00:17:30.783 --> 00:17:32.685
Find out before the live performance.

00:17:34.287 --> 00:17:37.356
But how do we do that?

00:17:38.157 --> 00:17:39.358
I hereby call this

00:17:39.425 --> 00:17:42.395
Operation
"Can We Make 1,000 Friends?"

00:17:42.495 --> 00:17:44.196
- A thousand friends?
- A thousand friends?

00:17:50.803 --> 00:17:53.072
- Please have a look.
- Please have a look.

00:17:53.139 --> 00:17:54.807
- We're NAZE.
- We're NAZE.

00:17:55.541 --> 00:17:57.777
- We have a live performance soon.
- Have a look.

00:17:57.843 --> 00:17:59.679
Please have a look!

00:17:59.745 --> 00:18:02.281
We're NAZE, a K-pop group!

00:18:02.615 --> 00:18:04.250
Please sign your name on the board

00:18:04.317 --> 00:18:05.851
if you would like to root for us.

00:18:05.918 --> 00:18:07.853
- Thank you! We're NAZE!
- Hey.

00:18:07.920 --> 00:18:09.121
This is super embarrassing.

00:18:09.188 --> 00:18:10.957
- Is there any point to this?
- Thank you.

00:18:11.023 --> 00:18:13.626
We even have to get 1,000 signatures.

00:18:14.293 --> 00:18:15.962
Guys!

00:18:16.295 --> 00:18:19.298
For the time being, let's trust
Mr. Azuma and do our best.

00:18:20.166 --> 00:18:21.567
Go!

00:18:21.634 --> 00:18:23.035
- Go!
- Go!

00:18:23.102 --> 00:18:24.971
- Please have a look!
- Please have a look!

00:18:25.404 --> 00:18:27.173
- Please have a look!
- We're NAZE, a K-pop group!

00:18:27.273 --> 00:18:30.009
You're Korean,
but you're doing K-pop in Japan?

00:18:30.076 --> 00:18:32.578
Well, there's a reason for that...

00:18:32.645 --> 00:18:35.281
He is an amazing singer.

00:18:35.348 --> 00:18:36.649
You'll be surprised

00:18:36.716 --> 00:18:38.818
- so please come to our show!
- Please!

00:18:38.884 --> 00:18:40.152
A live performance?

00:18:40.519 --> 00:18:42.622
But I already have my favorites.

00:18:43.089 --> 00:18:44.857
I'll have to spend time and money.

00:18:44.957 --> 00:18:47.360
I prefer to catch up on sleep
on my days off.

00:18:47.593 --> 00:18:49.295
I'm sorry. Good luck!

00:18:49.362 --> 00:18:51.030
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:18:51.931 --> 00:18:53.766
What? You're not Korean?

00:18:54.367 --> 00:18:55.401
No.

00:18:55.568 --> 00:18:57.503
There are so many Japanese people

00:18:57.570 --> 00:18:59.238
pretending to be Korean idols lately.

00:18:59.705 --> 00:19:01.374
I'm sorry.

00:19:01.474 --> 00:19:03.976
Hello, we're NAZE, a K-pop group.

00:19:04.076 --> 00:19:06.479
We'll be performing live,
so please come and watch.

00:19:06.545 --> 00:19:07.813
We look forward to seeing you.

00:19:07.880 --> 00:19:09.482
K-pop idols?

00:19:10.182 --> 00:19:12.918
You? But don't you look a bit plain?

00:19:12.985 --> 00:19:16.088
Right? We want our idols

00:19:16.155 --> 00:19:17.757
to look like princes, right?

00:19:17.823 --> 00:19:20.359
- Someone like TORINNER's Ryo.
- Gosh!

00:19:20.459 --> 00:19:22.528
- His looks are genius!
- National treasure level.

00:19:22.628 --> 00:19:24.930
- Yes, he's my favorite!
- He's amazing, right?

00:19:25.031 --> 00:19:26.298
So hot!

00:19:26.699 --> 00:19:29.635
But this boy here
looks pretty exotic.

00:19:29.702 --> 00:19:32.038
- Where are you from?
- Thailand.

00:19:32.138 --> 00:19:34.907
A Thai boy doing K-pop? Why?

00:19:35.007 --> 00:19:37.276
Why? I...

00:19:37.376 --> 00:19:39.278
I've loved it since I was a kid.

00:19:39.345 --> 00:19:43.115
Still, why go out of your way
to do Korean music?

00:19:43.182 --> 00:19:47.319
Yes, it feels a bit off
when a Thai boy does K-pop, right?

00:19:47.386 --> 00:19:48.387
Yes.

00:19:48.954 --> 00:19:51.724
- Well, whatever.
- Don't worry about it.

00:19:51.791 --> 00:19:53.125
Good luck.

00:19:53.192 --> 00:19:54.794
YUYA

00:19:56.429 --> 00:19:59.965
What's wrong with those women?
They're so mean!

00:20:00.066 --> 00:20:02.435
The world is so harsh.

00:20:02.535 --> 00:20:05.104
"You lack charm." "A Japanese person
pretending to be Korean."

00:20:05.171 --> 00:20:06.939
"Thai people don't suit K-pop."

00:20:07.039 --> 00:20:09.608
They're so unreasonable!
Just empty criticism!

00:20:09.675 --> 00:20:13.079
They should provide evidence
when they criticize people. Right?

00:20:13.145 --> 00:20:14.814
Just calm down.

00:20:14.880 --> 00:20:17.283
Getting upset about it now
won't help.

00:20:17.349 --> 00:20:18.718
I know, but...

00:20:20.352 --> 00:20:24.690
Mr. Azuma, do they have to continue
making those 1,000 friends?

00:20:24.857 --> 00:20:26.559
I'm against it.

00:20:26.859 --> 00:20:30.096
Making the boys listen to strangers
and their thoughtless opinions

00:20:30.429 --> 00:20:32.765
is just going to hurt them.

00:20:32.832 --> 00:20:36.168
But don't the opinions reflect
NAZE's reality right now?

00:20:36.469 --> 00:20:38.170
No evidence is stronger than that.

00:20:39.872 --> 00:20:41.073
Well...

00:20:41.640 --> 00:20:44.510
If someone asked you
to root for a random stranger

00:20:44.577 --> 00:20:45.578
would you want to?

00:20:46.979 --> 00:20:48.881
To be accepted by others

00:20:48.948 --> 00:20:51.717
they first need to understand
who they are.

00:20:52.218 --> 00:20:54.153
Sure, they'll hear things
they don't want to

00:20:54.754 --> 00:20:56.055
but that's unavoidable.

00:21:07.900 --> 00:21:11.237
Go home and rest today.
I'll stay and work.

00:21:11.837 --> 00:21:13.172
What?

00:21:36.896 --> 00:21:38.030
This is it.

00:21:39.698 --> 00:21:40.900
Good morning.

00:21:49.074 --> 00:21:50.242
Hey.

00:21:50.843 --> 00:21:53.145
Good morning...

00:22:08.894 --> 00:22:12.965
"Yearbooks, family photos,
home videos..."

00:22:14.400 --> 00:22:15.534
Morning.

00:22:19.071 --> 00:22:20.239
Good morning.

00:22:20.739 --> 00:22:23.042
You stayed here last night?
Are you okay?

00:22:23.142 --> 00:22:24.476
Yes, I'm okay.

00:22:26.312 --> 00:22:27.746
I came up with a great idea.

00:22:28.848 --> 00:22:30.216
Could you quickly gather

00:22:30.683 --> 00:22:32.685
the things on the list?

00:22:33.652 --> 00:22:34.820
What, these?

00:22:35.421 --> 00:22:36.655
Morning!

00:22:36.722 --> 00:22:38.424
- Good morning.
- Hey.

00:22:38.490 --> 00:22:41.060
We'll be using this
as the costume concept

00:22:41.727 --> 00:22:42.862
for the live performance.

00:22:44.730 --> 00:22:45.731
Are you serious?

00:22:46.065 --> 00:22:48.267
I've never seen stage costumes
like these before.

00:22:48.968 --> 00:22:50.169
Right?

00:22:50.236 --> 00:22:51.637
Wait, where are you going?

00:22:52.504 --> 00:22:54.840
Grocery shopping.
We'll be having a party tonight.

00:22:56.175 --> 00:22:58.010
TORINNER is so hot today!

00:22:58.077 --> 00:22:59.778
Ryo, you're so cute!

00:22:59.845 --> 00:23:01.380
Are they having
a live performance already?

00:23:01.447 --> 00:23:03.282
The managing team is so capable!

00:23:03.616 --> 00:23:05.417
Wait, they've set up a fan club.

00:23:05.484 --> 00:23:07.019
What? I want an early slot!

00:23:07.519 --> 00:23:10.389
How is the preparation for the first
live performance in Japan going?

00:23:10.456 --> 00:23:13.659
Over 10,000 people have applied
to join the fan club.

00:23:13.726 --> 00:23:16.095
The whole audience in the venue
will root for TORINNER.

00:23:16.829 --> 00:23:19.098
In addition,
the article we published beforehand

00:23:19.465 --> 00:23:21.800
made many fans see NAZE
as their enemies, as we wanted.

00:23:22.201 --> 00:23:23.202
In other words?

00:23:23.602 --> 00:23:26.305
As you've instructed,
NAZE will be crushed

00:23:27.172 --> 00:23:29.174
in this live performance.

00:23:31.877 --> 00:23:33.512
It doesn't matter how much it costs.

00:23:34.280 --> 00:23:36.282
Just make sure
you make absolutely no mistakes.

00:23:36.348 --> 00:23:37.449
Okay.

00:23:39.585 --> 00:23:43.689
I don't want anything to go wrong...

00:23:46.125 --> 00:23:48.027
and end up losing you.

00:23:52.164 --> 00:23:55.334
Yes. Certainly, sir.

00:23:55.801 --> 00:23:58.470
We'll make sure NAZE disappears
after the next live performance.

00:23:58.938 --> 00:24:00.973
What? Disappear?

00:24:01.507 --> 00:24:04.476
I don't see them as your rivals

00:24:04.543 --> 00:24:08.847
but it'd be annoying if they get
in the way of your Japan debut.

00:24:10.382 --> 00:24:12.284
You only need to do one thing.

00:24:12.851 --> 00:24:15.554
Show the audience an overwhelming
difference in your abilities.

00:24:16.088 --> 00:24:17.423
Use your perfect performance

00:24:17.489 --> 00:24:20.125
to show them you're
on a different level from NAZE.

00:24:20.192 --> 00:24:21.193
- Yes.
- Yes.

00:24:21.260 --> 00:24:25.965
Absolutely no mistakes are allowed.
Make very sure about that.

00:24:26.932 --> 00:24:28.600
If anyone makes a mistake

00:24:29.802 --> 00:24:31.737
he'll be removed
from TORINNER at once.

00:24:32.705 --> 00:24:33.706
- What?
- What?

00:24:41.647 --> 00:24:43.048
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

00:24:43.649 --> 00:24:45.284
- Excuse me!
- Excuse me!

00:24:45.985 --> 00:24:47.219
- Excuse me!
- Excuse me!

00:24:47.286 --> 00:24:48.454
Do you have a minute?

00:24:48.554 --> 00:24:51.724
I'm Kimkun,
a member of a group called NAZE.

00:24:51.790 --> 00:24:53.325
- Please have a look.
- Please root for us.

00:24:54.126 --> 00:24:57.529
Hello, we're NAZE.
Please have a look.

00:24:58.897 --> 00:25:00.399
We're K-pop group, NAZE.

00:25:00.466 --> 00:25:02.368
- Come here!
- We'll have a live performance soon.

00:25:02.434 --> 00:25:04.603
How many times do I need to tell you?

00:25:04.670 --> 00:25:07.539
The newbie just needs
to clean and do the dishes.

00:25:07.639 --> 00:25:09.775
You aren't allowed to cook yet!

00:25:09.842 --> 00:25:11.977
- But--
- Leave if you don't like it.

00:25:12.044 --> 00:25:14.346
You can be a chef
in your own country!

00:25:14.747 --> 00:25:17.850
How dare you sneak out ingredients?

00:25:17.916 --> 00:25:19.918
I'm the one who's going
to get yelled at by the owner!

00:25:28.360 --> 00:25:29.528
I believe you can make
your dreams come true!

00:25:33.032 --> 00:25:34.099
Aren't you cold?

00:25:35.601 --> 00:25:36.602
Yuya.

00:25:42.041 --> 00:25:43.809
You can't really see
the stars from here.

00:25:48.714 --> 00:25:52.918
I've always wanted
to become a K-pop star.

00:25:56.055 --> 00:25:57.823
When I was working in Thailand

00:25:58.991 --> 00:26:01.193
I was extremely poor

00:26:02.494 --> 00:26:05.531
but I held on to the dream
of being in K-pop someday

00:26:06.865 --> 00:26:07.866
and that kept me going.

00:26:11.503 --> 00:26:13.972
All the K-pop artists I looked up to

00:26:15.541 --> 00:26:17.443
were Koreans.

00:26:20.546 --> 00:26:24.016
I came to Korea
hoping to be like them.

00:26:25.551 --> 00:26:27.920
I practiced hard,
with almost no time to sleep.

00:26:29.855 --> 00:26:30.956
But...

00:26:40.265 --> 00:26:41.433
I wonder...

00:26:45.771 --> 00:26:48.307
Am I not allowed to be
in a K-pop group because I'm Thai?

00:26:50.476 --> 00:26:51.477
Would it be better...

00:26:53.912 --> 00:26:55.848
if I weren't in NAZE?

00:26:58.717 --> 00:26:59.985
That's not true.

00:27:01.186 --> 00:27:03.222
Turn, you're an amazing dancer.

00:27:04.456 --> 00:27:07.326
My brother is Japanese,
but he's popular.

00:27:09.561 --> 00:27:11.396
Nationality doesn't matter.

00:27:30.616 --> 00:27:31.717
But I...

00:27:36.421 --> 00:27:37.523
My looks...

00:27:38.891 --> 00:27:39.925
My singing skills...

00:27:40.826 --> 00:27:41.894
My dancing skills...

00:27:44.096 --> 00:27:45.864
There's nothing I can be proud of.

00:27:51.069 --> 00:27:54.573
Ever since I was a child, I've wanted
to be like my big brother.

00:27:57.943 --> 00:28:00.679
But no matter how hard I try,
I can never be better than him.

00:28:05.517 --> 00:28:06.985
Maybe I shouldn't...

00:28:08.787 --> 00:28:11.590
have the same dream as my brother.

00:28:25.370 --> 00:28:28.674
Hey, the miserable guys over there,
dinner is ready.

00:28:28.740 --> 00:28:31.843
Today, it's a special dish
made by the genius chef, Azuma.

00:28:37.015 --> 00:28:38.283
- Be careful.
- It's so dark.

00:28:38.617 --> 00:28:39.818
Is everyone here?

00:28:39.885 --> 00:28:42.354
- Mr. Azuma said we should sit here.
- Be careful.

00:28:42.454 --> 00:28:44.489
- Yes. Over here. Be careful.
- What's this?

00:28:47.326 --> 00:28:48.794
Thank you for waiting.

00:28:48.894 --> 00:28:50.996
This is today's specialty.

00:28:51.096 --> 00:28:52.497
Goodness, it's scary!

00:28:52.598 --> 00:28:54.166
Why is it so dark?

00:28:54.233 --> 00:28:57.302
This is a traditional
Japanese man's meal

00:28:57.369 --> 00:29:00.839
Japanese Yaminabe!

00:29:01.640 --> 00:29:03.242
Yaminabe?

00:29:03.475 --> 00:29:05.344
It's something like a game

00:29:05.410 --> 00:29:08.647
where we'd gather around a hot pot
and see who is the bravest.

00:29:08.947 --> 00:29:12.918
We'll blindly throw in
various things in the dark.

00:29:13.518 --> 00:29:17.256
The rule is, you must eat
whatever your chopsticks touch.

00:29:17.322 --> 00:29:18.624
Pranksters like to

00:29:18.690 --> 00:29:21.927
put terrible things
like frogs or shoe soles

00:29:21.994 --> 00:29:23.395
but you must never show fear.

00:29:23.996 --> 00:29:26.164
The Japanese man's meal
that tests your courage.

00:29:26.231 --> 00:29:28.033
That's Yaminabe!

00:29:28.133 --> 00:29:29.668
I don't want to eat that!

00:29:29.768 --> 00:29:32.738
- Are Japanese people crazy?
- We don't like it, either!

00:29:32.838 --> 00:29:33.972
Silence, all of you!

00:29:34.072 --> 00:29:36.441
You won't eat what I cooked?
You're fired, then!

00:29:36.541 --> 00:29:38.110
Disband now! You bunch of idiots!

00:29:38.477 --> 00:29:39.811
He's so unreasonable!

00:29:39.878 --> 00:29:42.047
True patience is enduring
what cannot be endured.

00:29:42.114 --> 00:29:44.316
Just try it.

00:29:46.585 --> 00:29:47.586
L-Let's eat.

00:29:50.155 --> 00:29:51.590
- I'm digging in.
- I'm digging in.

00:29:51.657 --> 00:29:53.125
Let's eat.

00:30:00.599 --> 00:30:02.000
What? It's good!

00:30:02.100 --> 00:30:03.535
- Yum!
- Not bad.

00:30:03.635 --> 00:30:06.305
- Absolutely delicious!
- Delicious!

00:30:06.371 --> 00:30:09.207
- It's Korean blood sausage. Right?
- I taste Japanese squid rice!

00:30:09.308 --> 00:30:10.709
There's Thai moo ping, too!

00:30:11.310 --> 00:30:13.412
Delicious! I want more!

00:30:15.280 --> 00:30:16.648
- Delicious!
- So good!

00:30:17.015 --> 00:30:20.052
The special Yaminabe
is delicious, isn't it?

00:30:20.118 --> 00:30:21.286
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:30:22.020 --> 00:30:26.191
Allow me, the genius chef Azuma,
to explain it to you, mere mortals.

00:30:26.258 --> 00:30:30.595
I used various food ingredients
from Korea, Thailand, and Japan

00:30:30.696 --> 00:30:35.500
and dozens of condiments, like miso,
soy sauce, kimchi, and nam pla

00:30:35.600 --> 00:30:37.803
to create
this ultimate mixed hot pot.

00:30:37.869 --> 00:30:38.870
Mixed?

00:30:38.937 --> 00:30:40.839
In Japan, we describe people
sharing the same experience

00:30:40.906 --> 00:30:42.641
as "eating from the same pot."

00:30:43.075 --> 00:30:44.443
How do you say it in Korean?

00:30:44.710 --> 00:30:46.945
(Korean)

00:30:47.346 --> 00:30:48.547
We have the same phrase in Thai.

00:30:48.647 --> 00:30:49.881
(Thai)

00:30:50.716 --> 00:30:53.151
Every country has a similar phrase.

00:30:53.218 --> 00:30:54.219
Interesting.

00:30:54.286 --> 00:30:57.089
Ever since you guys
were trainees in Seoul

00:30:57.155 --> 00:31:00.692
you've been living together
and eating the same food every day.

00:31:01.226 --> 00:31:02.527
It isn't just food.

00:31:03.028 --> 00:31:05.197
You've experienced moments
of happiness and sadness

00:31:05.630 --> 00:31:07.899
and overcame challenges together.

00:31:08.734 --> 00:31:13.171
Do your nationalities
really matter now?

00:31:15.107 --> 00:31:17.876
By combining various food ingredients

00:31:18.176 --> 00:31:20.045
we created a flavor
unique to this pot

00:31:20.112 --> 00:31:22.147
that can't be found
anywhere else in the world.

00:31:22.681 --> 00:31:26.084
Kimchi alone is spicy,
and nam pla alone is salty.

00:31:26.184 --> 00:31:29.421
But if we make good use
of their characteristics and mix them

00:31:29.488 --> 00:31:32.691
we create something that
is greater than the sum of its parts.

00:31:32.758 --> 00:31:35.827
Only the seven of you can create

00:31:36.228 --> 00:31:37.662
this one-of-a-kind flavor.

00:31:39.064 --> 00:31:42.667
And I'm here as the chef
to bring out that flavor.

00:31:43.568 --> 00:31:47.572
My seasoning will gradually
enhance your flavor.

00:31:48.273 --> 00:31:51.576
The origins of the ingredients
don't matter.

00:31:52.210 --> 00:31:55.614
There's no need to compare yourself
to others or imitate them, either.

00:31:57.215 --> 00:32:01.686
We'll bring out our unique flavor
with our own power.

00:32:02.921 --> 00:32:04.656
That's all that matters.

00:32:08.393 --> 00:32:09.561
Together

00:32:10.495 --> 00:32:13.698
let's create our own hot pot.

00:32:17.402 --> 00:32:18.737
Thank you.

00:32:20.038 --> 00:32:22.340
Thank you, Mr. Azuma.

00:32:22.674 --> 00:32:25.911
I went to the market early in the
morning and spent all day making this

00:32:25.977 --> 00:32:27.879
just to get this point across!

00:32:27.946 --> 00:32:29.448
So you'd better eat it all.

00:32:29.514 --> 00:32:31.516
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

00:32:33.618 --> 00:32:36.488
The origins of the ingredients
don't matter at all.

00:32:37.456 --> 00:32:39.591
Our unique flavor.

00:32:41.660 --> 00:32:43.161
I'm here!

00:32:44.763 --> 00:32:46.298
- Welcome back!
- Welcome back!

00:32:46.364 --> 00:32:48.166
Gosh, something smells delicious!

00:32:48.233 --> 00:32:50.969
Minase, your timing is perfect.
Eat with us.

00:32:51.269 --> 00:32:52.637
What's this?

00:32:53.138 --> 00:32:55.373
The special hot pot
made by the genius chef, Azuma.

00:32:55.474 --> 00:32:59.110
It's got frog, shoe sole,
plush toys--

00:32:59.177 --> 00:33:00.846
I'm not going to eat that!

00:33:02.647 --> 00:33:03.648
Have they arrived?

00:33:03.949 --> 00:33:06.218
I was told that
these are the stage costumes.

00:33:06.284 --> 00:33:08.119
Is this really what you ordered?

00:33:08.787 --> 00:33:12.457
They're perfect.
I call this "The Yaminabe Show".

00:33:12.958 --> 00:33:14.793
THE DAY OF THE PERFORMANCE

00:33:19.197 --> 00:33:21.933
- Isn't the merch this time awesome?
- I know!

00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:23.335
It's awesome, right?

00:33:25.537 --> 00:33:27.539
I don't see any of our fans.

00:33:28.740 --> 00:33:30.242
Today's show is special.

00:33:30.942 --> 00:33:33.445
Mr. Choi Ki-young
and the world will be watching.

00:33:34.312 --> 00:33:36.448
If you make a mistake,
you'll be fired immediately.

00:33:36.515 --> 00:33:38.216
Show them a perfect performance.

00:33:38.783 --> 00:33:39.784
- Okay!
- Okay!

00:33:52.631 --> 00:33:55.166
Goodness! He's so handsome today!

00:33:55.233 --> 00:33:57.536
Thank you for existing!

00:34:26.898 --> 00:34:28.600
Ryo is so cool.

00:34:29.234 --> 00:34:31.670
I hate to admit it,
but they're impressive.

00:34:41.546 --> 00:34:44.049
Ryo, I'll destroy you.

00:34:47.085 --> 00:34:48.353
His dance moves are different!

00:35:02.033 --> 00:35:03.234
Yeon-woo.

00:35:06.338 --> 00:35:07.706
Was that intentional?

00:35:19.818 --> 00:35:21.319
You're finished.

00:35:41.039 --> 00:35:42.340
With that foot...

00:35:43.308 --> 00:35:44.743
He won't be able to jump.

00:35:45.810 --> 00:35:47.312
We have to change the choreography.

00:35:51.916 --> 00:35:52.984
What's going on?

00:35:55.020 --> 00:35:56.454
What should I do?

00:35:57.622 --> 00:35:58.623
What should I do?

00:36:13.538 --> 00:36:14.639
LOOK AT ME FOR 3 SECONDS

00:36:31.723 --> 00:36:32.724
LOOK AT ME FOR 3 SECONDS

00:36:35.560 --> 00:36:36.594
You're so naive.

00:36:39.397 --> 00:36:41.066
- Come on, gather around.
- Together!

00:36:41.166 --> 00:36:42.567
Okay.

00:36:43.802 --> 00:36:45.904
TORINNER's performance was amazing.

00:36:46.871 --> 00:36:47.939
But...

00:36:50.375 --> 00:36:52.143
We just need to put on a performance

00:36:52.210 --> 00:36:53.378
that only we can do.

00:36:54.145 --> 00:36:55.413
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:36:56.881 --> 00:36:58.750
Okay, let's go!

00:36:59.417 --> 00:37:02.020
Our very own dream stage!

00:37:02.087 --> 00:37:03.455
Ready, go!

00:37:03.822 --> 00:37:05.256
- NAZE!
- NAZE!

00:37:05.523 --> 00:37:08.460
TORINNER was amazing.
I'm exhausted from all that cheering.

00:37:08.526 --> 00:37:09.928
Today's show was great.

00:37:10.595 --> 00:37:12.430
- Let's go home.
- Okay.

00:37:12.497 --> 00:37:13.898
I'm satisfied.

00:37:15.100 --> 00:37:16.434
What's playing?

00:37:24.709 --> 00:37:27.612
You get attention-seeking rookies
like them from time to time.

00:37:48.633 --> 00:37:50.135
I didn't see this coming.

00:38:09.788 --> 00:38:11.055
Darn those leftovers.

00:38:11.556 --> 00:38:12.757
Amazing!

00:38:27.972 --> 00:38:30.008
Wait, they're kind of cute.

00:38:38.550 --> 00:38:42.387
Wow, the audience
is paying attention.

00:38:42.453 --> 00:38:45.423
Nobody will root for you
if they don't know who you are.

00:38:45.490 --> 00:38:48.426
So we'll just tell them who NAZE is.

00:38:55.633 --> 00:38:57.769
They turned the crisis
into an opportunity.

00:39:00.638 --> 00:39:02.207
Is Azuma behind this?

00:39:05.643 --> 00:39:07.946
All right. This is where it begins.

00:39:52.690 --> 00:39:54.792
Hey, NAZE is kind of cute!

00:39:54.859 --> 00:39:57.128
I feel warm and fuzzy inside.

00:40:29.394 --> 00:40:30.662
You're so cute!

00:40:31.162 --> 00:40:32.163
Ready, go!

00:40:32.230 --> 00:40:34.365
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

00:40:41.105 --> 00:40:42.674
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

00:40:42.740 --> 00:40:44.642
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

00:40:44.742 --> 00:40:46.077
You're so cute!

00:40:49.847 --> 00:40:52.650
The performance was awesome!

00:40:53.651 --> 00:40:54.919
That's our genius.

00:40:55.820 --> 00:40:58.656
Now, it's time
for the finishing touch.

00:41:03.094 --> 00:41:04.429
Would you look at that?

00:41:05.463 --> 00:41:07.598
You're here, Ms. Park?

00:41:09.100 --> 00:41:12.570
We were told that our performance
would be kept a secret from you.

00:41:14.706 --> 00:41:15.974
Let's go.

00:41:18.576 --> 00:41:21.579
Let's consider today's result a draw.

00:41:23.614 --> 00:41:25.016
But...

00:41:25.550 --> 00:41:28.119
I won't forgive anyone
who makes a fool of my friends.

00:41:30.321 --> 00:41:31.990
I'll knock you out
if you do that again.

00:41:40.031 --> 00:41:41.966
He's so cool!

00:41:50.908 --> 00:41:53.878
The performance was great.
I'm impressed.

00:41:56.781 --> 00:41:58.049
I'm so sorry.

00:41:58.716 --> 00:41:59.884
I lied to you.

00:42:00.785 --> 00:42:03.021
Don't worry about that.
It was obvious from the start.

00:42:04.389 --> 00:42:08.659
But if you keep holding each other
back with stupid tricks on the stage

00:42:09.127 --> 00:42:10.962
we'll pull ahead of you in no time.

00:42:11.863 --> 00:42:12.864
What?

00:42:12.930 --> 00:42:16.801
He would've been badly injured
if he had done that acrobatic move.

00:42:19.737 --> 00:42:20.972
You noticed that much?

00:42:21.939 --> 00:42:23.908
You have more than just your looks.

00:42:24.008 --> 00:42:26.377
That's the brother Yuya is proud of.

00:42:31.349 --> 00:42:32.350
Let's go.

00:42:50.968 --> 00:42:52.470
You have a great team.

00:42:54.872 --> 00:42:55.873
Right?

00:42:57.175 --> 00:42:58.209
But...

00:42:59.177 --> 00:43:00.945
we won't lose next time.

00:43:03.181 --> 00:43:04.449
That's my line.

00:43:10.655 --> 00:43:12.423
Hey, Azuma!

00:43:12.490 --> 00:43:13.991
- What's up?
- The other day

00:43:14.058 --> 00:43:16.694
you said we'd make our hot pot.

00:43:16.761 --> 00:43:18.696
Does that mean
you want us to be a family?

00:43:19.063 --> 00:43:20.064
What?

00:43:20.131 --> 00:43:21.766
How did you reach that conclusion?

00:43:21.833 --> 00:43:23.201
Was that actually

00:43:23.267 --> 00:43:24.735
a proposal in disguise?

00:43:24.802 --> 00:43:25.803
You're an idiot.

00:43:25.870 --> 00:43:28.739
So, the two of them are still...

00:43:29.740 --> 00:43:32.343
Okay, things are going to get busy
from here on out.

00:43:33.111 --> 00:43:35.146
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

00:43:35.913 --> 00:43:37.615
NAZE, let's go!

00:43:37.682 --> 00:43:39.784
- Let's go!
- Go!

00:43:43.921 --> 00:43:47.558
This Empress of Japanese Showbiz
invited me to fight alongside her!

00:43:47.625 --> 00:43:49.227
There must be a catch. Don't do it.

00:43:49.327 --> 00:43:50.962
I discovered the boys

00:43:51.028 --> 00:43:52.430
who debuted as TORINNER!

00:43:52.497 --> 00:43:53.931
Gossip articles keep popping up.

00:43:54.031 --> 00:43:56.667
She must want to get rid of
both TORINNER and NAZE.

00:43:56.767 --> 00:43:58.836
There's nothing I can do this time.